The paper focuses on improving the performance of Batch Normalization in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel normalization method and discusses its theoretical analysis and experimental results, indicating that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of gradients, which suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on multiple computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
